From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: ci <ci@local>
Date: Wed, 20 May 2026 16:50:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] patches/0041-fman-pcd-kg-bind-port-widen-hwport-range.patch

PR14z12-D (2026-05-20): widen fman_pcd_kg_bind_port() port_id validator
from `> 10` to `> 0x3F` so it accepts BMI hwport_id values.

Background
----------
Patch 0040 (PR14z12-C) changed dpaa_get_fman_port_id() to return the BMI
port hwport_id (DTS cell-index of the fman-v3-port-rx node) instead of
the MAC cell-index, because KGAR walks fmkg_pe_sp[hwport_id] indexed by
the BMI hwport. On LS1046A the 10G RX ports at port@90000 / port@91000
have hwport_id 0x10 / 0x11 (= 16 / 17 decimal).

The matching validator inside fman_pcd_kg_bind_port() in patch 0006 was
authored against the old MAC-cell-index namespace (range 1..10) and was
NOT updated when patch 0040 switched the producer side to the BMI
namespace. Result observed on live DUT (2026-05-20):

  ask: hw: port-bind v4-TCP: kg_bind_port(port=16 dir=0) failed: -22
  ask: hw: port-bind v4-TCP: kg_bind_port(port=17 dir=1) failed: -22

i.e. -EINVAL from this validator, KG scheme never bound to ports,
fman_port_use_kg_hash() from PR14z7 never reached, silicon fully inert.

Fix
---
Widen the bound to 0x3F to match patch 0040's dpaa_get_fman_port_id()
upper bound. BMI hwport_ids on LS1046A FMan3 occupy 0x01..0x31:

  RX 1G  base 0x08, RX 10G base 0x10
  TX 1G  base 0x28, TX 10G base 0x30
  OH     base 0x02

0x3F gives headroom for a future SoC widening while still trapping
obviously-bogus values.
---
 drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/fman/fman_pcd_kg.c | 7 ++++++-
 1 file changed, 6 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/fman/fman_pcd_kg.c b/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/fman/fman_pcd_kg.c
index d0a21e9..85a6d3a 100644
--- a/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/fman/fman_pcd_kg.c
+++ b/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/fman/fman_pcd_kg.c
@@ -329,7 +329,12 @@ int err;
 
 if (!scheme)
 return -EINVAL;
-if (port_id == 0 || port_id > 10)
+/*
+ * PR14z12-D: port_id here is the BMI port hwport_id (DTS cell-index
+ * of fman-v3-port-rx / -tx), NOT the MAC cell-index. On LS1046A
+ * FMan3 the hwport_id range is 0x01..0x31; cap at 0x3F for headroom.
+ */
+if (port_id == 0 || port_id > 0x3F)
 return -EINVAL;
 
 fman = fman_pcd_get_fman(scheme->pcd);
